  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Kenya Cereal Value Chain Enhancement program</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project seeks to sustainably and inclusively increase access to markets for small holder farmers, increase incomes and enhance livelihoods resilience and food security status as well as stimulate growth of the local economies. The overall objective of the action is to develop an inclusive, resilient and sustainable green grams and sorghum value chain that improves the livelihoods of small scale farmers</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project seeks to sustainably and inclusively increase access to markets for small holder farmers, increase incomes and enhance livelihoods resilience and food security status as well as stimulate growth of the local economies. This will be achieved through enhancing production capacities of smallholder farmers by linking them to commercial extension service providers; strengthening of farmers&apos; capacity to participate in county agricultural forums, establishment and running of commercial aggregation centres that offers competitive prices to farmers</narrative>
  </description>
